  "body": "The function `compute_shuffled_index` seems to compute an useless addition. Here is the [definition](https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/blob/dev/specs/phase0/beacon-chain.md#compute_shuffled_index):\r\n```python\r\ndef compute_shuffled_index(index: uint64, index_count: uint64, seed: Bytes32) -> uint64:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Return the shuffled index corresponding to ``seed`` (and ``index_count``).\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    assert index < index_count\r\n\r\n    # Swap or not (https://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1007%2F978-3-642-32009-5_1.pdf)\r\n    # See the 'generalized domain' algorithm on page 3\r\n    for current_round in range(SHUFFLE_ROUND_COUNT):\r\n        pivot = bytes_to_uint64(hash(seed + uint_to_bytes(uint8(current_round)))[0:8]) % index_count\r\n        flip = (pivot + index_count - index) % index_count # <--- HERE\r\n        position = max(index, flip)\r\n        source = hash(\r\n            seed\r\n            + uint_to_bytes(uint8(current_round))\r\n            + uint_to_bytes(uint32(position // 256))\r\n        )\r\n        byte = uint8(source[(position % 256) // 8])\r\n        bit = (byte >> (position % 8)) % 2\r\n        index = flip if bit else index\r\n\r\n    return index\r\n```\r\nThe computation for the `flip` variable doesn't require the addition of `index_count` since the result is modulo `index_count`. So, the computation of the flip could be simplified to:\r\n```python\r\nflip = (pivot - index) % index_count\r\n```",
